Creating the Interview Activity - Page 2 of the dashboard. 21

Creating the 2nd page of the dashboard - Interview Activity

Find below the screenshots for creating the Interview Activity page of the Report.

Step 1. 

Duplicate page 1 to create page 2 like below:



Rename the page as Interview Activity.

Step 2. Change the name in the text box as Interview Activity Dashboard and move the Colaberry logo from Title text box to top left side as shown  in the screenshot below.



Delete all the KPI cards, but keep Interviews Per Day,% Interviewers Answered and% Interviewees Answered KPI cards to recreate the dashboard:

Rearrange the KPI cards:



Step 3.

Creating Interviews Per Day by Interviewer & Interviewee Line and Clustered Column Chart.

At the visualization pane of the dashboard, select the Line and clustered column chart.

Click on Year Month on the Date Table to go to the Shared axis.

From the Measure Table, Click on Interviews Per Day goes to the Column values.

% Interviewer Answered, and% Interviewee Answered both go to the Line values.




Formatting the visual:




In the format to turn off the data labels for Interviewer Answered and Interviewee Answered in the chart follow the screenshots below.


Create line and clustered column charts in Power BI

https://www.tutorialgateway.org/line-and-clustered-column-chart-in-power-bi/
